<font color="#FF0000">THE TREK TO TRAILS END</font><br>
<tt>Sun Oct 19 14:56:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
MTF,<br><br>
Maybe we have missed some of the wisdom of our ancestors.  They followed many a long hard path to the trail's end.  They expected hardship and planned quarters and resting-places along the way.  When they did not respect the changing elements and obstacles they knew must come they failed.  Sometimes with fatal results.<br><br>
We must choose our paths carefully and when the time comes throw in our own winter quarters or rest stop for the more modern thinkers.<br><br>
When we bog down in our quilt, diverse opinions, or just become fed up with the road we must stop reflect, play, but come back to the road.<br><br>
We have started down many good paths and due this discourse we find we abandon the trail.<br><br>
What comes when all the good trails are gone?  We should think long on this.  Some of our brothers are making the choice to abandon the trail while the others struggle to blaze new trail when only a weak enemy blocks the others.<br><br>
We are men, Warriors, and people of vision.<br><br>
We are Brothers of Choice.<br>

